<div id="review_3727886245" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3727886245" />
    <a title="Luís" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/117399210-lu-s"><img alt="Luís" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1620236159p2/117399210.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3727886245?book_show_action=true">Dec 30, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Luís" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Luís" href="/user/show/117399210-lu-s">Luís</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140140354" href="/book/show/849126.Haroun_and_the_Sea_of_Stories">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=adventure">adventure</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=magical-realism">magical-realism</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=iraq-india-israel">iraq-india-israel</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/117399210-lu-s?shelf=children">children</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3727886245" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11273819928946621871">Everything was going well in Haroun&apos;s life until his mother left with the neighbour and Rachid, his father and king of storytellers, lost his temper. But Rachid has contracts to respect: the 1st is a disaster, and Haroun fears the worst for the 2nd. But during the night preceding this fatal day, Haroun discovers the marvellous world of the sea of ​​tales where he will live extraordinary adventures. Rachid found inspiration and Haroun (and his city) the joy of living;<br/>It is a wonderful story that </span>
  <span id="freeText11273819928946621871" style="display:none">Everything was going well in Haroun's life until his mother left with the neighbour and Rachid, his father and king of storytellers, lost his temper. But Rachid has contracts to respect: the 1st is a disaster, and Haroun fears the worst for the 2nd. But during the night preceding this fatal day, Haroun discovers the marvellous world of the sea of ​​tales where he will live extraordinary adventures. Rachid found inspiration and Haroun (and his city) the joy of living;<br />It is a wonderful story that Salman Rushdie wrote for his son with kind geniuses, somewhat narrow-minded officials, crooked politicians, lots of fabulous characters (mechanical birds, talkative fish, floating gardener ...) and an awful cult guru who wants poison tales. This story can be read on several levels: simple entertaining tale, a satire of some quirks of our modern society through not really recommendable politicians or a scary cult guru, storey of a loving son who wants to do everything to help his dad.<br />I liked this story which smells sweetly of the magical tales of the past. I noted with amusement that the bird chosen by Haroun is the hoopoe which has been the guide bird par excellence since "The Conference of the Birds" by the Persian poet Farîd al-Dîn Attâr.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11273819928946621871" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
